(337,15150,'172. R. Groenboom and G. Renardel de Lavalette. A Formalization of Evolving Alge-bras. In Proceedings of Accolade95. Dutch Research School in Logic, 1995.The authors present the syntax and semantics for a Formal Language for EvolvingAlgebra (FLEA) covering sequential ASMs. This language is then extended to amulti-modal language FLEA? and it is sketched how one can transfer the axiomsBoerger E.: The Origins and the Development of the ASM Method ...54of the logic MLCM to FLEA?. MLCM is a Modal Logic of Creation and Modi?ca-tion, a dynamic logic which is incorporated in Jonker?s Common Object-OrientedLanguage for Design COLD [142, 143]. See [290].',0,0),
