(337,15173,'195. Y. Gurevich and D. Rosenzweig. Partially Ordered Runs: A Case Study. In Y.Gurevich and P. Kutter and M. Odersky and L. Thiele, editor, Abstract State Ma-chines: Theory and Applications, volume 1912 of LNCS, pages 131?150. Springer-Verlag, 2000.Boerger E.: The Origins and the Development of the ASM Method ...57The ASM investigation [83] of Lamport?s Bakery Algorithm is sharpened in termsof partially ordered runs, abstracting from the mapping of moves to linear real-time. Some properties are proved which are useful for reasoning about partiallyordered runs. The paper also appeared as technical report in TIK-Report 87,ETH Zu¨rich, March 2000, and in MSR-TR-99-98.',0,0),
