(337,15182,'203. H. Hinrichsen. Formally Correct Construction of a Pipelined DLX Architecture.Technical Report TR 98-5-1, Darmstad University of Technology, Dept. of Elec-trical and Computer Engineering, 1998.In an e-mail to B¨orger on February 11, 1998, Hinrichsen points out that for acorrect handling of the instruction sequence 1. LOAD R1,A, 2. LOAD R2, B, 3.ADD R3,R1,R2, the ADD instruction must be stalled for one clock cycle. Thiscorrects an omission of a hazard case in the last re?nement step of [88].',0,0),
