(337,15242,'260. A. Poetzsch-He?ter. Prototyping Realistic Programming Languages Based OnFormal Speci?cations . Acta Informatica , 34:737?772, 1997.A tool supporting the generation of language-speci?c software from speci?cationsis presented, enabling in particular the generation and re?nement of interpretersBoerger E.: The Origins and the Development of the ASM Method ...65based on formal language speci?cations. Static semantics is de?ned by an attribu-tion technique (e.g. for the speci?cation of ?ow graphs). The dynamic semantics isde?ned by ASMs. As an example, an object-oriented programming language withparallelism is speci?ed. Part of this work has appeared as TR 93-1396 of CornellUniversity and in 1994 as Developing E?cient Interpreters based on Formal Lan-guage Speci?cations in P. Fritzson (Ed.): Compiler Construction, Springer LNCS786, pages 233-247.',0,0),
(337,15243,'261. A. Prinz. Formal Semantics for SDL. De?nition and Implementation. Habilita-tionsschrift, Humboldt University of Berlin, Germany, 2000.Contains a complete de?nition and implementation of the static and dynamicsemantics of a characteristic sublanguage of SDL.',0,0),
